Version 1.2.0-beta.1
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Released: 2026-04-29

Features:
 * OSC 11 dynamic background color — apps like neovim and theme-switching
   scripts can now change the terminal background at runtime via the OSC 11
   escape sequence; reset with OSC 111
 * enable-wide-handle defaults to true so the splitter between split
   terminals is easier to see and grab on dark themes and HiDPI displays
 * Auto-equalize panes on split and close, sway-style
 * Documentation site at https://gwelr.github.io/ttyx_/
 * Sensitive values redaction: passwords, tokens and proxy credentials are
   stripped from trace logs, command-line argv and hyperlink click events
   before reaching any log sink

Bugfixes:
 * Maximized terminal now correctly restores when loading a saved session;
   fixes a long-standing bug pre-existing since the upstream Tilix 2017
   implementation
 * Trigger templates: $0 now correctly substitutes the whole match (was
   shifted by one due to a size_t underflow); user templates relying on the
   bugged behaviour need indices shifted up by one
 * Triggers with an unrecognised action name are now skipped with a warning
   instead of silently rewritten to UpdateState
 * Paste hardening: strip OSC, DCS, APC and PM escape sequences from
   clipboard content before paste
 * Robust /proc/[pid]/stat parser with bounds validation
 * Password manager delete now correctly reports keyring failures and
   handles legacy Tilix-schema entries
 * Proxy URL builder: percent-encode userinfo and drop the redundant leading
   @; HTTPS proxy now receives credentials when configured

Miscellaneous:
 * First beta of the 1.2.0 release; validation period before GA
 * Internal refactors using D SumType for compile-time exhaustiveness:
   TerminalRegex (BuiltinRegex/CustomRegex), SyncInputEvent, and a typed
   TerminalSnapshot struct as the single source of truth for session
   serialisation
 * CI: install LDC from the upstream tarball; build GtkD from source on
   Debian Testing where the apt package was removed

Version 1.1.1
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Released: 2026-04-18

Features:
 * Automatic config migration from Tilix — on first run, ~/.config/tilix/ is
   copied to ~/.config/ttyx/ with the original kept as backup
 * Password manager reads legacy com.gexperts.tilix.Password schema for
   backwards compatibility; new passwords are saved under the ttyx schema
 * TTYX_ID environment variable set in shells alongside TILIX_ID for
   backwards compatibility with existing shell integrations

Bugfixes:
 * Color scheme loader no longer shows duplicates; user config now wins
   over system defaults when a scheme filename exists in both
 * Post-install script writes a minimal index.theme at the install prefix
   so gtk-update-icon-cache can generate a valid icon cache
 * AppStream metadata no longer includes stale Tilix release entries

Miscellaneous:
 * Rename user-visible Tilix references: Nautilus menu, shortcuts window,
   GSettings descriptions, icon filenames, log and temp paths
 * Rewrite man page under ttyx_ identity; drop 30 stale translations that
   referenced Tilix-branded msgids
 * Release process simplified: drop hand-assembled binary tarball, ship
   only Flatpak bundle with signed checksums
 * Add Troubleshooting section to README (stale icon cache, Wayland Quake)
 * Add ROADMAP.md documenting vision and phase plan

Version 1.1.0
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Released: 2026-04-15

Features:
 * Security: enforce in-memory-only scrollback, capped at 256-999999 lines
 * Security: core dump protection via prctl PR_SET_DUMPABLE
 * Security: Secure Clear action (Ctrl+Shift+L) to wipe scrollback buffer
 * Security: SSH session detection indicator for ssh, scp, sftp, mosh, sshfs
 * Security: clipboard auto-clear after configurable timeout
 * Security: strip bracketed paste escape sequences to prevent injection
 * Security: multi-line paste review dialog before execution
 * Security: expanded dangerous command detection (sudo, rm -rf, curl|bash, etc.)
 * Security: per-paste unsafe warning (no longer permanently dismissed)
 * Security: all options consolidated in Advanced preferences with descriptions
 * Flatpak packaging with GNOME 48 SDK and bundled LDC compiler
 * ProcessMonitor optimization: idle CPU reduced from 1.4% to 0.1%

Bugfixes:
 * Fix GC crash when opening preferences on GLib 2.84+
 * Fix SSH and root indicators not clearing when process exits
 * Fix color scheme test when schemes not installed in XDG paths

Miscellaneous:
 * Major terminal.d decomposition into extracted components
 * Replace applyPreference switch with PreferenceRegistry pattern
 * 119 unit tests covering security, clipboard, rendering, and monitoring
 * CI: add xvfb support for GTK integration tests
